import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['population'] = pd.to_numeric(data['population'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='population', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['population'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['population'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across zip codes?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['city'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common city name in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['city'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.legend([f"Max: {data['city'].value_counts().max():.2f}"])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['income'] = pd.to_numeric(data['income'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('zip_code')['income'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='zip_code', y='income', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average income of households in each zip code?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
